00:18:14,784 --> 00:18:17,466
for ground excursions led by Mr. Conrad.

258
00:18:17,671 --> 00:18:18,778
Major Jack Chapman.

259
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:21,320
All right. Once on the island...

260
00:18:21,345 --> 00:18:23,993
the storm interference will block
all radio contact with the ship.

261
00:18:24,032 --> 00:18:25,946
That means, we will be by ourselves

262
00:18:26,413 --> 00:18:29,018
Three days later, refuel team will meet us
here on

263
00:18:29,043 --> 00:18:30,106
north end of the island.

264
00:18:30,307 --> 00:18:32,126
That might be our only safe departure...

265
00:18:32,151 --> 00:18:33,561
for unknown period of time.

266
00:18:34,479 --> 00:18:35,963
So a tip for everybody...

267
00:18:36,821 --> 00:18:38,923
Don't miss it, please.

268
00:19:00,496 --> 00:19:01,637
What are you doing down here?

269
00:19:02,641 --> 00:19:04,268
I could ask you the same thing.

270
00:19:05,862 --> 00:19:08,233
Why does a geological mapping mission
needs explosives.

271
00:19:10,393 --> 00:19:12,682
Seismic charges for the geological survey.

272
00:19:12,952 --> 00:19:14,661
Uh-huh. You believe that?

273
00:19:14,686 --> 00:19:16,079
I didn't say that.

274
00:19:16,229 --> 00:19:18,131
Have you met Colonel Packard yet?

275
00:19:18,332 --> 00:19:19,333
Yeah.

276
00:19:19,401 --> 00:19:20,983
The guy is bound pretty tight

277
00:19:21,183 --> 00:19:24,488
But as a decorated war hero.
It's the package they come in

278
00:19:25,189 --> 00:19:26,289
And you?

279
00:19:27,392 --> 00:19:30,462
Isn't shooting a mapping mission
a step down for a photojournalist?

280
00:19:30,664 --> 00:19:33,101
The right photo can help shape opinions.

281
00:19:33,126 --> 00:19:34,628
And win you a Pulitzer.

282
00:19:34,653 --> 00:19:36,750
Okay, Captain Conrad.

283
00:19:36,950 --> 00:19:38,051
What about you?

284
00:19:38,153 --> 00:19:40,487
How did British Special
forces get dragged into this?

285
00:19:40,687 --> 00:19:42,493
Just Conrad. I'm decommissioned.

286
00:19:44,336 --> 00:19:45,511
They offered me money.

287
00:19:45,712 --> 00:19:47,203
You don't strike me as a mercenary.

288
00:19:47,304 --> 00:19:49,197
You don't strike me as a war photographer.

289
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:51,908
Anti-war photographer.

290
00:20:13,216 --> 00:20:14,324
What are you writing there, Chap?

291
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:16,456
Letter to my boy.

292
00:20:16,689 --> 00:20:18,088
DEAR BILLY

293
00:20:18,936 --> 00:20:20,123
"Dear Billy...

294
00:20:20,148 --> 00:20:23,328
"I know I said I would at be home by your
birthday, but I lied straight to your face.

295
00:20:23,528 --> 00:20:24,803
"I'm a terrible dad.

296
00:20:25,005 --> 00:20:26,446
"I hope this letter makes out for it".

297
00:20:27,612 --> 00:20:29,205
It's too short.

298
00:20:56,279 --> 00:20:59,057
This storm look a lot nastier in person.

299
00:20:59,082 --> 00:21:01,422
maybe we should consider
postponing the mission.

300
00:21:01,829 --> 00:21:03,130
How far away is this island?

301
00:21:03,155 --> 00:21:05,113
50 miles. maybe more.

302
00:21:05,214 --> 00:21:06,579
Take us closer.

303
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:08,276
You wanna launch, you do it from here.

304
00:21:08,476 --> 00:21:10,117
Can you punch through that, Colonel?

305
00:21:10,295 --> 00:21:12,489
- Our opening is now.
- Through this hole right here?

306
00:21:12,690 --> 00:21:14,372
Yeah, it's a real low pressure pocket.

307
00:21:14,452 --> 00:21:16,385
I appreciate your passion, Randa...

308
00:21:16,486 --> 00:21:18,404
but as a field supervisor of
the controlling agency...

309
00:21:18,604 --> 00:21:20,854
I say we abort. that's it,
we are gonna abort.

310
00:21:21,297 --> 00:21:22,499
Wise call.

311
00:21:22,524 --> 00:21:25,051
I'm sure the Landsat inspector
will be inspired by your courage.

312
00:21:25,386 --> 00:21:27,188
I hope he's inspired by my common sense.

313
00:21:27,270 --> 00:21:28,675
This is only a map survey.

314
00:21:28,776 --> 00:21:31,577
To one of the last unchartered areas
on the face of the earth.

315
00:21:31,678 --> 00:21:33,112
And you want to call it on account of rain?

316
00:21:33,313 --> 00:21:34,620
Stay on the boat if you want to.

317
00:21:34,821 --> 00:21:37,513
It could be years
before we get another shot at this.

318
00:21:38,036 --> 00:21:41,291
I'm told your unit is capable
of handling inclement weather, Colonel.

319
00:21:42,093 --> 00:21:45,149
Why don't we leave it to Colonel Packard
to break the tie?

320
00:21:46,646 --> 00:21:49,294
There is no way
I'm getting on that helicopter.

321
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:58,008
We did ask on those helicopters.
Should not they know why?

322
00:21:58,209 --> 00:22:00,302
Why? And raise an alarm?

323
00:22:01,104 --> 00:22:02,987
It is purely a precaution, Brooks.

324
00:22:05,064 --> 00:22:06,065
Right.

325
00:22:06,167 --> 00:22:07,836
Two mike to launch.

326
00:22:10,630 --> 00:22:12,174
Two mike to launch.

327
00:22:21,710 --> 00:22:23,259
Still this end to come

328
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:26,590
Nothing he wouldn't do himself.
He is taking the lead.

329
00:22:26,791 --> 00:22:28,754
That means he miss his bed, I miss my bed.

330
00:22:28,956 --> 00:22:29,957
Don't you miss your bed?

331
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,791
Do you even have a bed, Cole?

332
00:22:34,914 --> 00:22:36,631
You got a bed, right?

333
00:22:37,632 --> 00:22:39,275
See you at the rendevzous, Chapman.

334
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:40,768
Yes sir.

335
00:22:43,313 --> 00:22:44,313
SEISMIC LOADS

336
00:22:56,638 --> 00:22:59,652
Complete FOB lockdown, and clear the deck.

337
00:22:59,753 --> 00:23:00,954
One mike to launch.

338
00:23:01,498 --> 00:23:02,406
- Battery?
- Check.

339
00:23:02,506 --> 00:23:04,455
- Generator start?
- Check.

340
00:23:04,556 --> 00:23:06,457
- Engine start?
- Checked three times.

341
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:10,873
This is Fox. Leader of the Fox Group.

342
00:23:11,072 --> 00:23:12,576
It's time once again...

343
00:23:12,677 --> 00:23:14,602
Griffin and ants show.

344
00:23:14,801 --> 00:23:16,727
As usual, remember...

345
00:23:16,928 --> 00:23:19,749
... Hold on to your butts!

346
00:23:21,436 --> 00:23:24,584
Attention pilots. You are clear to takeoff.

347
00:23:25,583 --> 00:23:27,542
Launch, launch, launch.

348
00:23:48,022 --> 00:23:49,551
Combat formation.

349
00:23:50,587 --> 00:23:52,160
Keep visual.

350
00:23:52,361 --> 00:23:54,654
Fox five let me know when you're close.

351
00:23:57,254 --> 00:23:59,323
Fox Five is in the slot.

352
00:23:59,524 --> 00:24:00,526
Roger that.

353
00:24:01,127 --> 00:24:04,192
Fox Team, follow up on me. Keep together.

354
00:24:09,432 --> 00:24:10,534
Let's do this!

355
00:24:19,957 --> 00:24:21,783
Maintain course.

356
00:24:22,085 --> 00:24:23,727
Nothing we haven't done before.

357
00:24:24,939 --> 00:24:26,377
"Dear Billy.

358
00:24:26,956 --> 00:24:29,624
"You ever look inside a hurricane
and decide?

359
00:24:29,826 --> 00:24:32,081
"Maybe I should fly straight through it."

360
00:24:32,282 --> 00:24:34,324
"Because that is what just happen."

361
00:24:38,048 --> 00:24:40,057
You might want to hang on.

362
00:25:04,590 --> 00:25:06,104
Fox Leader to Fox Group.

363
00:25:06,306 --> 00:25:07,706
Switch to inertial navigation.

364
00:25:09,443 --> 00:25:11,595
And remember the story of Icarus...

365
00:25:11,596 --> 00:25:14,643
whose father gave him wings, they flex.

366
00:25:14,857 --> 00:25:17,291
Warned him not to fly too close to the sun.

367
00:25:18,330 --> 00:25:20,340
But the exhilaration was too great.

368
00:25:20,540 --> 00:25:22,839
So he flew higher and higher...

369
00:25:23,441 --> 00:25:25,996
until the sun melted his wings...

370
00:25:26,697 --> 00:25:28,753
and he fell into the sea.

371
00:25:30,285 --> 00:25:33,958
The US Army is not an irresponsible father.

372
00:25:34,159 --> 00:25:37,996
So they gave us wings to fight hot hobo.

373
00:25:38,197 --> 00:25:40,079
Pennsylvania steel.

374
00:25:41,009 --> 00:25:44,374
Guaranteed not to melt.

375
00:26:29,781 --> 00:26:32,053
Oh wait, that's pretty, huh?

376
00:26:37,458 --> 00:26:39,009
Let's take him low and level.

377
00:27:21,258 --> 00:27:23,112
Fox Leader to Fox Group.

378
00:27:23,409 --> 00:27:25,710
Clear up, survey as told.

379
00:27:26,811 --> 00:27:28,173
Fox Seven, prepare set her on deck.

380
00:27:29,322 --> 00:27:31,721
Copy Fox Leader. Proceedl to Zone Six.

381
00:27:31,996 --> 00:27:33,191
Put us down over there.

382
00:27:33,896 --> 00:27:35,620
Everyone else, stay with the team leader.

383
00:27:38,623 --> 00:27:41,585
Gears, get it, Come on,
Let's move it!

384
00:28:00,991 --> 00:28:02,024
READY SYSTEM

385
00:28:02,925 --> 00:28:04,824
Ready for seismic chargers.

386
00:28:05,239 --> 00:28:06,240
Roger that.

387
00:28:09,060 --> 00:28:10,528
Fox Group, let it fly.

388
00:28:19,069 --> 00:28:22,019
Copy all. Fox Three. Heading 0-9-0.

389
00:28:24,671 --> 00:28:26,030
Are you seeing what I seeing?

390
00:28:27,231 --> 00:28:30,735
The seismic response is incredible.

391
00:28:39,854 --> 00:28:42,057
Hey, Randy, you're not gonna believe this.

392
00:28:42,305 --> 00:28:43,476
The bedrock,

393
00:28:44,277 --> 00:28:45,686
It's practically hollow.

394
00:28:57,299 --> 00:28:58,610
Incoming!

395
00:29:11,523 --> 00:29:12,668
Look out!

396
00:29:59,414 --> 00:30:01,107
On guard, Fox Five!

397
00:30:01,207 --> 00:30:03,335
Fox Eight is down! Four Fox is down!

398
00:30:03,537 --> 00:30:05,169
Respond, Fox Three!

399
00:30:12,621 --> 00:30:13,622
Oh My God!

400
00:30:16,217 --> 00:30:17,759
Does anyone know what that is?

401
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:20,362
I don't know, man. God dammit...

402
00:30:20,563 --> 00:30:22,597
Three km west of LD.

403
00:30:22,798 --> 00:30:24,201
Jesus! I never saw anything like it!

404
00:30:27,030 --> 00:30:28,723
Roger

405
00:30:46,639 --> 00:30:47,799
Is that a monkey?

406
00:30:47,952 --> 00:30:49,406
What the hell is that?

407
00:30:49,731 --> 00:30:51,372
Somebody talk to me, man.

408
00:30:51,572 --> 00:30:53,773
Turn right to 2-5-0. Visual contact.

409
00:30:53,973 --> 00:30:55,326
Fox Leader to Fox Group.

410
00:30:55,526 --> 00:30:58,120
Form a perimeter. Ready gunners position.

411
00:30:58,571 --> 00:31:02,273
Shit!

412
00:31:02,474 --> 00:31:05,878
Fox leader to Fox Group. Fire at will!

413
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:09,769
- What the hell is that?
- I don't know!

414
00:31:27,413 --> 00:31:28,788
Pull out now. Pull out.

415
00:31:28,988 --> 00:31:30,109
I don't take orders from you!

416
00:31:30,190 --> 00:31:31,301
Get us the hell out of here!

417
00:31:31,501 --> 00:31:32,502
Fox Nine is down!

418
00:31:36,879 --> 00:31:38,975
Fox Six, we got ** trouble.

419
00:31:39,783 --> 00:31:40,784
We are going down.

420
00:31:45,596 --> 00:31:48,641
Fox Five, this is Fox leader.
Fox Nine is down.

421
00:31:48,867 --> 00:31:50,562
1 klik north of the river bed.

422
00:31:50,761 --> 00:31:52,026
Insert recovery team.

423
00:31:52,937 --> 00:31:54,668
Fox Five is hovering.

424
00:31:55,473 --> 00:31:56,867
We got men going out the door.

425
00:32:00,069 --> 00:32:01,386
I need help here. I need...

426
00:32:01,622 --> 00:32:02,706
Shit!

427
00:32:11,116 --> 00:32:12,644
Kill this son of a bitch.

428
00:32:15,087 --> 00:32:16,088
Pull up!

429
00:32:24,407 --> 00:32:25,528
Brace for impact!

430
00:32:31,368 --> 00:32:32,911
Mayday! Mayday! Mayday!

431
00:32:34,462 --> 00:32:36,180
Yourself, you idiot!

432
00:32:47,205 --> 00:32:48,206
Watch out!

433
00:32:51,657 --> 00:32:53,106
Oh God!

434
00:32:55,409 --> 00:32:57,061
Prepare to crash!

435
00:32:57,261 --> 00:32:58,262
Brace!

436
00:33:07,171 --> 00:33:08,371
Fox Leader is down!

437
00:33:08,572 --> 00:33:10,273
Fox Five in bound to pick up!

438
00:33:10,473 --> 00:33:11,775
We have him in sight.

439
00:33:11,974 --> 00:33:14,844
Hold tight, Colonel Packard,
We're on our way!

440
00:33:20,047 --> 00:33:21,803
Hang on, Briggs. I'm coming.

441
00:33:34,616 --> 00:33:35,917
Going down.

442
00:33:36,118 --> 00:33:38,118
I repeat, we are going down!

443
00:33:40,322 --> 00:33:42,724
Listen, I want you to tell
me something right now.

444
00:33:42,923 --> 00:33:44,462
- Do you love your mama?
- I love her!

445
00:33:44,671 --> 00:33:46,993
- How much do you love your mama?
- I love her so much.

446
00:35:09,015 --> 00:35:11,417
Calling all units! Is anybody airborne?

447
00:35:11,616 --> 00:35:13,820
I repeat, is anybody airborne?

448
00:35:14,621 --> 00:35:17,572
They're all down. Everyone.

449
00:35:18,673 --> 00:35:20,404
We are on the south side of the island.

450
00:35:20,603 --> 00:35:22,582
There is a river a couple
of klicks from here.

451
00:35:22,782 --> 00:35:25,785
If we sticks to its bank, we make it
to the EXFIL site on the north shore.

452
00:35:25,984 --> 00:35:28,991
And then what? All our choppers are down.

453
00:35:29,191 --> 00:35:30,713
We'll find a way to signal the ship.

454
00:35:30,797 --> 00:35:34,416
They'll send a search party.
We just have to make it by the exit window.

455
00:35:35,517 --> 00:35:37,332
I should be sitting at a desk.

456
00:35:37,531 --> 00:35:39,671
are we just not gonna talk about this?

457
00:35:40,130 --> 00:35:42,681
My best guess is
we're scattered over 4 to 5 miles radius.

458
00:35:42,881 --> 00:35:45,284
We must head north and join anyone we find.

459
00:35:45,483 --> 00:35:46,601
Are you alright?

460
00:35:46,802 --> 00:35:48,515
I don't know how to answer
that question right now.

461
00:35:48,715 --> 00:35:50,415
I don't know what that was either.

462
00:35:50,615 --> 00:35:53,533
All that money that they paid you?
I hope you're worth it.

463
00:35:54,376 --> 00:35:56,278
You really not gonna talk about it?

464
00:35:56,479 --> 00:35:59,507
You know, this is not normal, right?
Stuff like that doesn't just happen!

465
00:36:01,559 --> 00:36:03,410
This is Fox Leader to Fox group.

466
00:36:03,609 --> 00:36:07,100
Anybody with ears, ** respond.

467
00:36:07,300 --> 00:36:08,849
Flex, Chapman.

468
00:36:09,049 --> 00:36:10,259
Fox Six, Chapman.

469
00:36:10,459 --> 00:36:11,560
Say again your last.

470
00:36:11,762 --> 00:36:13,991
4 klicks west, the highest peak in..

471
00:36:14,193 --> 00:36:16,693
November Alpha 3-0-0. Out.

472
00:36:16,893 --> 00:36:19,797
Roger that, Chapman.
West highest mountain peak.

473
00:36:19,997 --> 00:36:21,053
Oliver.

474
00:36:21,254 --> 00:36:23,791
Fox Six confirmed, we're the Sea Stallion.

475
00:36:23,991 --> 00:36:26,192
Chapman, hold your position.

476
00:36:26,392 --> 00:36:28,195
We will go to you. There is not

477
00:36:28,395 --> 00:36:30,161
on that sea stallion to kill this thing.

478
00:36:30,361 --> 00:36:32,010
Survey your perimeter.

479
00:36:32,210 --> 00:36:34,332
Locate possible ambush sites. Over.

480
00:36:36,646 --> 00:36:37,647
Chapman.

481
00:36:39,964 --> 00:36:40,965
Reles.

482
00:36:40,990 --> 00:36:43,290
Taking a non R day, you're good to go

483
00:36:43,492 --> 00:36:46,192
I'm good to go sir, sir. Get him up.

484
00:36:48,629 --> 00:36:50,047
Chapman, all stations.

485
00:36:50,247 --> 00:36:51,648
Recon the environment.

486
00:37:07,787 --> 00:37:09,368
Cole, what's wrong with you?

487
00:37:09,579 --> 00:37:11,380
How you even got an appetite right now?

488
00:37:14,484 --> 00:37:15,984
Eating is for the living.

489
00:37:16,192 --> 00:37:19,553
We just got taken down by a monkey
this size of a building!

490
00:37:19,886 --> 00:37:20,888
Yeah!

491
00:37:22,174 --> 00:37:24,677
That was an unconventional encounter.

492
00:37:25,078 --> 00:37:28,030
Is that really all your brain
telling yourself right now?

493
00:37:28,430 --> 00:37:29,732
There was no tactical precedents.

494
00:37:29,932 --> 00:37:32,034
We did the best we could in the situation.

495
00:37:34,188 --> 00:37:35,789
Griffin. Cole.!

496
00:37:42,637 --> 00:37:44,568
Thank God you guys are okay!

497
00:37:47,871 --> 00:37:49,524
Good to see you, sir..

498
00:37:50,225 --> 00:37:51,526
How many left?

499
00:37:51,726 --> 00:37:53,333
Seven survivors.

500
00:37:53,533 --> 00:37:55,434
Seven confirmed KIA.

501
00:37:58,390 --> 00:37:59,692
Slivko, and the rest are unknown.

502
00:38:14,306 --> 00:38:15,608
Where is Randa?

503
00:38:18,552 --> 00:38:19,553
How you doing?

504
00:38:20,152 --> 00:38:21,253
I'm fine. Thank you.

505
00:38:21,278 --> 00:38:22,279
Good.

506
00:38:22,385 --> 00:38:24,252
Glad to hear it. I was worried about you.

507
00:38:29,095 --> 00:38:33,282
You are going to tell me
everything I do not know...

508
00:38:33,382 --> 00:38:35,394
or I'm gonna blow your head off.

509
00:38:37,507 --> 00:38:39,689
Monsters exists.

510
00:38:39,890 --> 00:38:40,932
No shit.

511
00:38:41,769 --> 00:38:42,795
Nobody believed me.

512
00:38:43,666 --> 00:38:45,502
Yesterday, I was a crackpot.

513
00:38:46,272 --> 00:38:47,776
But today.

514
00:38:47,922 --> 00:38:50,725
So, This was never about geology.

515
00:38:51,497 --> 00:38:53,989
You dropped those charges
to flush something out.

516
00:38:54,906 --> 00:38:55,957
Who are you?

517
00:38:56,057 --> 00:38:58,515
You heard of the USS Lawton?

518
00:38:58,727 --> 00:39:00,275
Neither did the public

519
00:39:00,464 --> 00:39:04,447
Out of the thousand young men on that ship
I was the only survivor.

520
00:39:04,647 --> 00:39:06,730
They told my family she
was sunk in battle...

521
00:39:06,755 --> 00:39:08,236
but I know what I saw.

522
00:39:08,261 --> 00:39:10,062
It had no conscience.

523
00:39:10,939 --> 00:39:13,269
No reasoning, just destroy

524
00:39:13,570 --> 00:39:15,371
I spent the last 30 years...

525
00:39:15,396 --> 00:39:18,298
trying to prove the truth of what
I learned that day.

526
00:39:19,309 --> 00:39:22,013
This planet doesn't belong to us.

527
00:39:22,046 --> 00:39:26,351
ancient species owned this earth
long before mankind.

528
00:39:26,552 --> 00:39:28,828
And if we keep our heads
buried in the sand...

529
00:39:28,853 --> 00:39:30,153
they will take it back

530
00:39:30,829 --> 00:39:32,531
My agency is known as Monarch.

531
00:39:32,556 --> 00:39:36,160
We specialize in the hunt for
massive unidentified terrestrial organisms

532
00:39:36,536 --> 00:39:38,537
You knew that thing was out here?

533
00:39:38,562 --> 00:39:41,598
I'm sorry for your men, Colonel.
I truly am.

534
00:39:42,798 --> 00:39:45,590
Get us home with proof.

535
00:39:46,392 --> 00:39:48,444
So we can send the cavalry.

536
00:40:00,671 --> 00:40:01,851
I'm the cavalry.

537
00:40:03,563 --> 00:40:05,173
It's called the Hollow Earth Theory.

538
00:40:05,198 --> 00:40:06,802
Randa hired me...

539
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:08,524
because I wrote paper...

540
00:40:08,724 --> 00:40:11,826
Substantiating what most people think
is a crackpot idea.

541
00:40:12,027 --> 00:40:15,512
That there is this massive
underground spaces

542
00:40:15,537 --> 00:40:18,011
- Isolated from the surface world.
- has it ways.

543
00:40:18,036 --> 00:40:20,534
Randa believed this island
may be one of those.

544
00:40:20,606 --> 00:40:23,098
An emergence point for
whatever lives below.

545
00:40:23,361 --> 00:40:25,844
ancient species like what we just saw.

546
00:40:26,044 --> 00:40:27,806
I thought he was out of his mind.

547
00:40:28,762 --> 00:40:30,262
This is Slivko, do you read?

548
00:40:30,287 --> 00:40:31,288
Anybody out there?

549
00:40:31,481 --> 00:40:33,284
We are headed north of the EXFIL location

550
00:40:33,482 --> 00:40:36,181
Everyone here seems way too calm right now.

551
00:40:36,367 --> 00:40:38,401
You copy? Anybody?

552
00:40:38,426 --> 00:40:39,248
We're out of range, Slivko.

553
00:40:39,450 --> 00:40:40,452
Shit.

554
00:40:40,552 --> 00:40:42,414
Save it for when we get
closer to the group.

555
00:40:54,025 --> 00:40:55,527
Nobody move.

556
00:40:58,329 --> 00:40:59,332
Easy.

557
00:41:15,146 --> 00:41:17,374
- Silvko.
- What?

558
00:41:22,330 --> 00:41:23,731
Put it down.

559
00:41:45,253 --> 00:41:48,257
These men did not die in vain.

560
00:41:49,459 --> 00:41:51,360
I swear to God...

561
00:41:51,560 --> 00:41:55,564
Their deaths will not go unanswered.

562
00:42:00,029 --> 00:42:03,104
Now, Let's get to Chapman
and those munitions.

563
00:42:10,788 --> 00:42:13,891
You ever heard of the story of the
mouse, lion and the thorn?

564
00:42:14,601 --> 00:42:15,701
Yeah.

565
00:42:15,900 --> 00:42:17,101
There you go then.

566
00:42:17,435 --> 00:42:19,438
In case we ever see that primate again.

567
00:42:20,410 --> 00:42:23,394
You do know that the story is about a mouse
who turn a friend with a lion...

568
00:42:23,419 --> 00:42:25,721
after taking out the thorn
out of his paw, right?

569
00:42:27,121 --> 00:42:28,544
No it's not.

570
00:42:28,597 --> 00:42:30,699
The mouse kills the lion with the thorn.

571
00:42:32,517 --> 00:42:34,018
Who told you that, Cole?

572
00:42:35,049 --> 00:42:36,450
My mother.

573
00:42:41,369 --> 00:42:42,969
That actually explains a lot.

574
00:43:09,838 --> 00:43:11,238
Watch out those tree!

575
00:43:11,438 --> 00:43:12,741
- Let's go come on!
- What is that?

576
00:43:12,941 --> 00:43:14,944
Watch your six!

577
00:43:15,143 --> 00:43:17,025
Up In the trees!

578
00:43:24,231 --> 00:43:25,232
Cole!

579
00:43:25,683 --> 00:43:26,684
No!

580
00:43:27,545 --> 00:43:28,545
We got you!

581
00:43:29,646 --> 00:43:30,925
I can't get a shot!

582
00:43:35,630 --> 00:43:38,635
Cut off the legs!

583
00:44:07,546 --> 00:44:08,647
I have you!

584
00:44:34,896 --> 00:44:37,897
Take it out, guys! Move out

585
00:44:42,685 --> 00:44:43,685
Stay tight

586
00:44:50,394 --> 00:44:51,994
What the hell is this?

587
00:45:39,040 --> 00:45:40,041
Go, Behind you!

588
00:45:40,742 --> 00:45:41,842
Stay Calm.

589
00:45:42,044 --> 00:45:43,045
Conrad.

590
00:45:43,245 --> 00:45:44,544
Stay back!

591
00:45:45,190 --> 00:45:46,192
Guys.

592
00:45:48,673 --> 00:45:49,676
Nobody shoot! Nobody shoot.

593
00:46:01,383 --> 00:46:03,034
No. No need for that.

594
00:46:03,235 --> 00:46:04,336
Come on now!

595
00:46:04,536 --> 00:46:06,912
Everybody keep your wigs on now!

596
00:46:08,541 --> 00:46:09,542
What?

597
00:46:10,062 --> 00:46:12,105
I did not believe it
when they said you would come.

598
00:46:13,306 --> 00:46:14,508
I was up all night...

599
00:46:14,708 --> 00:46:17,872
Just thinking about how me and Gunpein
dreamt to this moment.

600
00:46:18,693 --> 00:46:19,993
And now here it is.

601
00:46:20,019 --> 00:46:22,020
Twenty-eight years, 11 months...

602
00:46:22,222 --> 00:46:24,736
8 failed attempts to get back to the world

603
00:46:24,937 --> 00:46:26,638
and instead, the world comes to me?

604
00:46:27,534 --> 00:46:28,634
Ain't that a crack?

605
00:46:30,736 --> 00:46:32,139
They never smile.

606
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:34,641
Did you crash here?

607
00:46:35,441 --> 00:46:36,642
Sorry miss.

608
00:46:36,841 --> 00:46:39,591
Lt. Hank Marlow of the 45th.

609
00:46:45,033 --> 00:46:47,735
You are more beautiful..

610
00:46:47,935 --> 00:46:50,487
Than a hot dog and a beer...

611
00:46:50,688 --> 00:46:53,291
At Wrigley Field on opening day.

612
00:46:59,758 --> 00:47:01,569
But you are real.

613
00:47:03,870 --> 00:47:04,912
Right?

614
00:47:07,315 --> 00:47:09,216
I told you. Did not I tell you?

615
00:47:09,423 --> 00:47:10,624
I Said...

616
00:47:10,824 --> 00:47:12,127
"It's fine".

617
00:47:13,526 --> 00:47:15,330
There we go.

618
00:47:19,009 --> 00:47:20,611
There's something out there, man.

619
00:47:21,201 --> 00:47:22,702
There is a lot out there.

620
00:47:23,447 --> 00:47:25,050
Now, Come on. We gotta get home.

621
00:47:26,283 --> 00:47:27,885
You don't want to be out here at night.

622
00:50:19,324 --> 00:50:22,383
You probably noticed a lot of weird things
on this Island

623
00:50:23,799 --> 00:50:27,203
As long as we stay in here,
where the people live, we'll be alright.

624
00:50:28,614 --> 00:50:29,792
That wall...

625
00:50:30,344 --> 00:50:32,583
Is that supposed to keep out that thing?

626
00:50:32,814 --> 00:50:35,666
No, he's not the one
we're trying to keep out.

627
00:50:37,123 --> 00:50:38,268
What?

628
00:50:38,569 --> 00:50:41,918
These people live up in the top of the
trees, while we are down in the roots.

629
00:50:42,158 --> 00:50:44,273
Some of them don't even seem to age.

630
00:50:45,299 --> 00:50:46,480
No crime...

631
00:50:46,664 --> 00:50:48,342
No personal property.

632
00:50:49,092 --> 00:50:50,350
They're past all that.

633
00:51:03,205 --> 00:51:05,371
Thank you.
Thank you.

634
00:51:07,049 --> 00:51:08,796
So Good news.

635
00:51:09,103 --> 00:51:10,923
They say you can shack up here.

636
00:51:12,882 --> 00:51:14,551
I didn't hear them say anything.

637
00:51:14,908 --> 00:51:16,810
They don't speak too much.

638
00:51:17,109 --> 00:51:21,050
been here as I long as I have,
you will start to understand, you'll see.

639
00:51:21,075 --> 00:51:22,203
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

640
00:51:22,636 --> 00:51:25,078
We can not stay here.
We have to get off the island.

641
00:51:25,269 --> 00:51:26,694
We have lives.
I have a life.

642
00:51:26,719 --> 00:51:29,795
Nieves now is not the time. Alright?

643
00:51:30,031 --> 00:51:31,946
What lands here tends to stay here.

644
00:51:34,555 --> 00:51:35,612
As far as I can tell...

645
00:51:35,637 --> 00:51:38,418
this ship washed up about 10 years
before I did.

646
00:51:38,703 --> 00:51:40,179
You've been here since '44?

647
00:51:40,409 --> 00:51:41,111
Yeah

648
00:51:41,311 --> 00:51:43,237
And What happened with the war? Do we win?

649
00:51:43,489 --> 00:51:44,490
Which one?

650
00:51:45,654 --> 00:51:46,942
That makes sense.

651
00:51:48,390 --> 00:51:49,841
This is all halo ground to them.

652
00:51:49,866 --> 00:51:51,896
So if you like your hands,
don't touch anything.

653
00:52:07,908 --> 00:52:09,285
Look at that.

654
00:52:23,756 --> 00:52:26,790
The way they tell it,
for thousands of years...

655
00:52:26,815 --> 00:52:29,005
the people of this island lived in fear

656
00:52:30,587 --> 00:52:32,981
It's hell of a long time to be scared.

657
00:52:36,603 --> 00:52:39,478
And then one day,
the damnest thing happened.

658
00:52:40,012 --> 00:52:41,894
Some of the things they were afraid of...

659
00:52:41,919 --> 00:52:45,009
Started protecting against the things
that were eating them.

660
00:52:47,382 --> 00:52:49,543
But nothing lasts forever, I guess.

661
00:52:56,020 --> 00:52:59,060
And this is where they honor
the last of their saviors.

662
00:53:06,303 --> 00:53:07,305
Yeah.

663
00:53:08,579 --> 00:53:09,756
That's Kong.

664
00:53:13,853 --> 00:53:15,480
He is king down here.

665
00:53:18,261 --> 00:53:20,065
He is God to these people.

666
00:53:22,141 --> 00:53:24,025
Kong is a pretty good king.

667
00:53:24,685 --> 00:53:26,332
he's to himself mostly

668
00:53:29,570 --> 00:53:33,150
This is his home. We are just guests here.

669
00:53:34,891 --> 00:53:38,602
But you don't go into someone's house
and start dropping bombs...

670
00:53:38,627 --> 00:53:39,960
unless you're picking a fight.

671
00:53:40,789 --> 00:53:42,958
Was it Kong the one who killed your friend?

672
00:53:44,567 --> 00:53:45,568
No.

673
00:53:47,344 --> 00:53:48,560
One of them did.

674
00:53:50,369 --> 00:53:52,396
Kong is God on the island...

675
00:53:53,074 --> 00:53:55,051
but the devils live below us.

676
00:53:56,654 --> 00:53:57,842
And what are they called?

677
00:54:00,135 --> 00:54:01,571
The Iwis won't speak their name.

678
00:54:02,504 --> 00:54:04,732
But I call skull crawlers.

679
00:54:04,972 --> 00:54:06,169
Why?

680
00:54:06,836 --> 00:54:07,981
Cause it's sounds unique.

681
00:54:10,837 --> 00:54:11,558
Okay.

682
00:54:11,583 --> 00:54:14,630
I just made that name up.
I am trying to scare you.

683
00:54:14,672 --> 00:54:15,674
I'm trying calling them that.

684
00:54:15,784 --> 00:54:16,913
- Are you feeling it?
- Yes...

685
00:54:17,277 --> 00:54:18,798
- I like the name...
- It's very good.

686
00:54:19,097 --> 00:54:22,555
I never said the name out loud Before
it sounds stupid now that I say just..

687
00:54:22,881 --> 00:54:24,260
You call them whatever you want.

688
00:54:24,884 --> 00:54:27,204
Big lizard things. Nasty.

689
00:54:28,415 --> 00:54:30,133
They come from the vents.

690
00:54:30,158 --> 00:54:32,040
Deep down.
That's why Kong got so mad.

691
00:54:34,801 --> 00:54:36,775
Cause bombs woke up a bunch of them.

692
00:54:40,344 --> 00:54:42,527
I tell you what, you're luckey.
He's out there too

693
00:54:42,848 --> 00:54:44,414
or you would not have made it this far.

694
00:54:45,559 --> 00:54:48,770
Crafty bastards. Neat as hell.

695
00:54:53,190 --> 00:54:56,773
He can handle those **
when they're still small.

696
00:55:00,346 --> 00:55:02,215
You don't want to wake up the big one.

697
00:55:02,519 --> 00:55:03,961
- How big is it?
- It's bigger than...

698
00:55:04,349 --> 00:55:06,007
The White daughter's whole family.

699
00:55:06,351 --> 00:55:09,086
Kong is the last of its kind
but he's still growing.

700
00:55:09,111 --> 00:55:10,557
And you better hope he does.

701
00:55:10,755 --> 00:55:12,636
Because the Iwis say once Kong goes...

702
00:55:13,171 --> 00:55:15,215
Then the big one comes out.

703
00:55:16,478 --> 00:55:18,082
And it's good night Irene.

704
00:55:19,521 --> 00:55:21,142
Listen, There is a refueling team...

705
00:55:21,191 --> 00:55:23,723
coming to the north end of the island
in three days.

706
00:55:23,997 --> 00:55:25,299
You should come with us.

707
00:55:25,672 --> 00:55:27,161
At the north end of the island?

708
00:55:28,601 --> 00:55:29,602
We're gonna get out of here.

709
00:55:29,762 --> 00:55:31,372
- In three days?
- Yes.

710
00:55:37,519 --> 00:55:39,787
We can't get to the north
end in three days.

711
00:55:40,032 --> 00:55:42,807
It is impossible. That's it. No way.

712
00:55:46,850 --> 00:55:48,321
At least not on foot

713
00:56:12,082 --> 00:56:14,785
That is one ugly ass bird.

714
00:56:31,471 --> 00:56:32,478
Dear Billy...

715
00:56:32,846 --> 00:56:34,480
this place is hell.

716
00:56:37,089 --> 00:56:38,559
The monsters exists.

717
00:56:38,973 --> 00:56:40,690
Under beds they sign the pay checks

718
00:56:41,819 --> 00:56:43,020
- Come on, man.
- It seems like...

719
00:56:43,290 --> 00:56:46,508
Maybe he want's to go kill that ape
instead of get ourselves out of here?

720
00:56:46,533 --> 00:56:46,994
Yeah!

721
00:56:47,083 --> 00:56:48,144
Are we gonna make it?

722
00:56:48,194 --> 00:56:50,031
- Make what?
- The EXFIL!

723
00:56:50,298 --> 00:56:51,807
We getta be there in three days!

724
00:56:51,894 --> 00:56:53,130
We'll make it, we're gonna make it.

725
00:56:53,222 --> 00:56:55,023
Yeah, Cole but what happened to Chapman...?

726
00:56:55,048 --> 00:56:57,271
Colonel said he is there.
he's there.

727
00:57:03,852 --> 00:57:04,853
We were this close...

728
00:57:04,878 --> 00:57:05,909
to get it working.

729
00:57:05,933 --> 00:57:09,224
Gunpei and we're gonna take off
to the open sea trying to get home.

730
00:57:09,585 --> 00:57:11,310
And one of that things got him.

731
00:57:14,523 --> 00:57:15,797
There she is.

732
00:57:26,962 --> 00:57:28,414
Well that's lovely.

733
00:57:31,272 --> 00:57:32,626
Damn right.

734
00:57:41,316 --> 00:57:42,918
Is this thing even float?

735
00:57:43,544 --> 00:57:46,721
Me and Gunpei spent six years of our lives
buliding this thing.

736
00:57:48,124 --> 00:57:49,917
It is called the Great Fox.

737
00:57:50,415 --> 00:57:51,696
And she floats.

738
00:58:01,829 --> 00:58:03,447
I pulled the engine parts from my P-51...

739
00:58:03,595 --> 00:58:04,909
His old Zero.

740
00:58:05,336 --> 00:58:07,601
On a B-29 on the beach
one day out or something.

741
00:58:07,840 --> 00:58:09,285
You gotta be kidding me.

742
00:58:09,478 --> 00:58:11,725
This machine is made out of pure tetanus.

743
00:58:13,404 --> 00:58:14,752
I know she isn't pretty to look at...

744
00:58:15,126 --> 00:58:17,451
but it's nothing a couple of
extra hands can't fix it.

745
00:58:17,854 --> 00:58:20,604
Unless you got a better idea,
I suggest we get cracking

746
00:58:23,349 --> 00:58:24,351
Alright.

747
01:00:00,028 --> 01:00:02,273
Come on, get up!

748
01:01:08,693 --> 01:01:11,323
Well, look at that.

749
01:01:11,979 --> 01:01:13,092
It bleeds.

750
01:01:15,952 --> 01:01:17,419
We did that.

751
01:01:17,936 --> 01:01:19,473
We hook up with Chapman...

752
01:01:19,498 --> 01:01:22,461
There is enough munition
on that down Sea Stallion...

753
01:01:22,486 --> 01:01:24,063
to finish the job.

754
01:01:31,302 --> 01:01:32,501
Magnificent.

755
01:01:33,115 --> 01:01:35,431
You know why I carry this
instead of an M-16?

756
01:01:37,265 --> 01:01:39,848
I took it off a farmer
who fight for the NVA.

757
01:01:40,146 --> 01:01:42,219
He surrendered right after
we levelled his village.

758
01:01:42,730 --> 01:01:44,148
He was 50 years old.

759
01:01:44,173 --> 01:01:45,895
Saying that he haven't see a gun
till we showed up.

760
01:01:46,324 --> 01:01:49,540
Sometimes, the enemy does not exist...

761
01:01:50,564 --> 01:01:52,243
until you are looking for one.

762
01:01:53,362 --> 01:01:55,862
What happens
when they show up on your door step?

763
01:01:55,938 --> 01:01:57,602
I'll still have his gun.

764
01:01:59,289 --> 01:02:01,792
Best of luck with that, soldier.

765
01:02:10,801 --> 01:02:13,549
Okay. So they have got 48 hours
to make it to the North Shore.

766
01:02:13,839 --> 01:02:15,632
Slivko, do you wanna get Jenny back then?

767
01:02:15,657 --> 01:02:17,468
Yeah, pop's a mechanic.

768
01:02:17,493 --> 01:02:18,815
I can't fix this, he'll disown me.

769
01:02:20,155 --> 01:02:21,842
He never sees me again.

770
01:02:22,276 --> 01:02:23,653
Hold up on that, Churchill.

771
01:02:23,987 --> 01:02:26,028
Russia was our ally.

772
01:02:26,053 --> 01:02:27,614
Now You say we're at war with them?

773
01:02:27,962 --> 01:02:29,449
It is more of a cold war.

774
01:02:29,499 --> 01:02:30,717
The Cold War like...

775
01:02:31,222 --> 01:02:32,761
That they take the summers off?

776
01:02:35,086 --> 01:02:37,504
What about the Cubs?
The cubs win a world series yet?

777
01:02:37,529 --> 01:02:38,530
The Cubs?

778
01:02:38,789 --> 01:02:39,870
No, not even close.

779
01:02:40,166 --> 01:02:41,208
Were they ever good?

780
01:02:41,233 --> 01:02:43,086
Happens to be my team. Where are you from?

781
01:02:43,156 --> 01:02:44,946
- Detroit.
- Okay.

782
01:02:44,971 --> 01:02:46,981
The tigers there.
They win all this year?

783
01:02:47,453 --> 01:02:49,157
- I do not know.
- I doubt it. Yeah.

784
01:02:50,998 --> 01:02:53,087
Hey, what do you think will win a fight?
A tiger or a Cub?

785
01:02:54,082 --> 01:02:55,311
A tiger will win.

786
01:02:56,349 --> 01:02:58,938
Yeah, because the cubs are baby bear.

787
01:02:59,066 --> 01:03:01,742
A full grown tiger can eat a baby bear.

788
01:03:02,676 --> 01:03:03,921
Think it through.

789
01:03:05,294 --> 01:03:07,433
We also put a man on the moon.

790
01:03:08,022 --> 01:03:09,598
No kidding

791
01:03:09,764 --> 01:03:11,354
What did they do? Just leave him up there?

792
01:03:11,850 --> 01:03:13,230
What's he eating?

793
01:03:13,406 --> 01:03:16,088
Tang. Spam

794
01:03:17,724 --> 01:03:19,384
Come on, we are losing daylight.

795
01:03:25,726 --> 01:03:28,117
Fox leader. this is Chapman, over.

796
01:03:28,894 --> 01:03:30,453
Fox leader. this is Chapman, over.

797
01:03:41,422 --> 01:03:42,566
Dear Billy...

798
01:03:43,587 --> 01:03:46,136
Sometimes life just punch you in the balls

799
01:03:47,131 --> 01:03:48,132
Dammit.

