Not Randa.

813
01:05:14,245 --> 01:05:17,521
The one guy in the crowd
who actually took me seriously.

814
01:05:17,829 --> 01:05:19,240
It felt good.

815
01:05:19,265 --> 01:05:21,593
Then I thought he was crazy
when he said there are those monsters.

816
01:05:23,127 --> 01:05:24,553
I can't tell when I am talking...

817
01:05:24,943 --> 01:05:26,424
- Or when I am not talking.
- You are talking.

818
01:05:26,763 --> 01:05:27,764
- Really?
- Yes.

819
01:05:27,854 --> 01:05:29,511
- I'm talking?
- Yes.

820
01:05:29,536 --> 01:05:30,684
Your mouth is moving

821
01:05:30,970 --> 01:05:31,971
What?

822
01:05:32,048 --> 01:05:34,146
I'm gonna stab you by the end of the night.

823
01:05:34,729 --> 01:05:35,738
Really?

824
01:05:36,819 --> 01:05:38,117
Just kidding.

825
01:05:42,325 --> 01:05:44,527
If the boat does not work,
we just take the train.

826
01:05:46,194 --> 01:05:50,567
Is not it odd, most dangerous places,
aurora is the most beautiful?

827
01:05:51,355 --> 01:05:54,167
I'm trying to take a
long exposure photograph

828
01:05:54,488 --> 01:05:55,809
but my flashlight broke

829
01:05:59,085 --> 01:06:00,086
Try this.

830
01:06:00,877 --> 01:06:01,878
Thank you.

831
01:06:04,683 --> 01:06:06,541
- Royal Air Force?
- My father's.

832
01:06:06,805 --> 01:06:10,139
He threw it to me from the train
as he rolled off to fight with the Nazis.

833
01:06:11,004 --> 01:06:13,087
He's like John Wayne to me.

834
01:06:13,642 --> 01:06:15,226
Took our mythic hero.

835
01:06:16,682 --> 01:06:18,003
Did he come back?

836
01:06:18,338 --> 01:06:20,792
His plane went down near Hamburg.

837
01:06:21,166 --> 01:06:23,034
They searched for him for months but...

838
01:06:27,153 --> 01:06:29,666
I suppose no man comes home from war.

839
01:06:31,186 --> 01:06:32,284
Not really.

840
01:06:41,633 --> 01:06:44,650
Mills, quit dickin' around.
I going off perimeter.

841
01:06:55,866 --> 01:06:56,957
Colonel Packard...

842
01:06:58,893 --> 01:07:02,821
this mission to the crash site is **

843
01:07:04,532 --> 01:07:06,933
I understand going after your man.

844
01:07:08,036 --> 01:07:09,499
But the rest of it...

845
01:07:11,219 --> 01:07:12,698
This is beyond us

846
01:07:14,267 --> 01:07:16,351
You do not like the way I'm running things?

847
01:07:17,225 --> 01:07:18,985
Then you know where the door is.

848
01:07:21,013 --> 01:07:24,217
You set this in motion
when you put this place on the map.

849
01:07:24,469 --> 01:07:27,243
And I will not cut and run.

850
01:07:30,063 --> 01:07:32,522
I know an enemy when I see it.

851
01:08:00,518 --> 01:08:02,961
This man's name was Gunpei Ikari.

852
01:08:06,346 --> 01:08:07,974
If you take away the uniforms...

853
01:08:08,898 --> 01:08:09,924
and the war...

854
01:08:11,428 --> 01:08:13,078
Then he became my brother.

855
01:08:16,148 --> 01:08:18,558
And we swore
we'd never leave each other behind

856
