Yes!

918
01:13:04,492 --> 01:13:05,728
We are going home!

919
01:13:12,481 --> 01:13:13,529
Man Down!

920
01:13:24,053 --> 01:13:25,379
What the hell, man?

921
01:13:26,015 --> 01:13:27,125
He is gone.

922
01:13:27,517 --> 01:13:30,420
Everybody grab your gear.
We have to keep moving.

923
01:13:31,418 --> 01:13:32,966
We go ashore
meet up with Packard

924
01:13:32,991 --> 01:13:34,826
No. Wait a minute!

925
01:13:35,046 --> 01:13:37,335
Is nobody gonna say anything about the...?

926
01:13:37,402 --> 01:13:38,403
He is gone!

927
01:13:38,773 --> 01:13:41,078
And he ain't coming back.
There is nothing to say.

928
01:13:44,164 --> 01:13:45,365
Oh my...

929
01:13:50,342 --> 01:13:52,400
That flare was only 2 clicks north

930
01:13:53,672 --> 01:13:55,004
They should be here soon.

931
01:13:55,376 --> 01:13:58,098
Unless the were eaten by something
that's bigger than us.

932
01:14:05,275 --> 01:14:06,538
Fuck!
Oh, shit.

933
01:14:06,563 --> 01:14:07,916
Slivko!

934
01:14:09,471 --> 01:14:10,793
I thought I'd not see you guys again.

935
01:14:10,863 --> 01:14:12,987
- I thought you were crazy.
- I wish I had been.

936
01:14:13,285 --> 01:14:15,086
- What's the count?
- What you see...

937
01:14:15,367 --> 01:14:16,369
It is what we got.

938
01:14:16,525 --> 01:14:17,526
We lost one too.

939
01:14:17,765 --> 01:14:19,155
Good to see you fellas!

940
01:14:19,865 --> 01:14:20,936
Who the hell is this?

941
01:14:20,961 --> 01:14:22,461
Heads up to hitchhiker.

942
01:14:22,594 --> 01:14:25,797
Lieutenant Hank Marlow
of the 45th suit sqaddron of the 15th.

943
01:14:25,822 --> 01:14:27,630
You've been here since World War II?

944
01:14:27,981 --> 01:14:29,975
Yes sir. I missed the parade?

945
01:14:30,739 --> 01:14:31,739
I'll be damned.

946
01:14:32,054 --> 01:14:33,487
Snap to. Lieutenant.

947
01:14:33,953 --> 01:14:35,195
We're gonna get him home, sir.

948
01:14:35,819 --> 01:14:36,830
We follow this river...

949
01:14:36,855 --> 01:14:38,897
We'll make it to the boat,
we'll make it to the north shore in time.

950
01:14:39,112 --> 01:14:40,496
That sounds good.

951
01:14:41,038 --> 01:14:42,157
But we're not leaving yet.

952
01:14:42,182 --> 01:14:44,181
We still got a man out there, Conrad.

953
01:14:44,753 --> 01:14:46,108
Wait a second. You got someone out there?

954
01:14:46,182 --> 01:14:47,147
Chapman.

955
01:14:47,158 --> 01:14:49,033
he is with the Down Sea Stallion,
Just west of it.

956
01:14:49,313 --> 01:14:51,086
West? We can't go west!

957
01:14:51,436 --> 01:14:52,920
That's where those skull things live.

958
01:14:53,227 --> 01:14:55,889
We have a old saying here.
"East is best, west is worst!".

959
01:14:55,948 --> 01:14:57,029
That's why we say it!

960
01:14:57,070 --> 01:14:58,691
A little southwest...

961
01:14:59,053 --> 01:15:00,446
We could talk about that

962
01:15:00,471 --> 01:15:02,508
But we are gonna need a lot more guns
if we're gonna go west.

963
01:15:03,217 --> 01:15:06,157
Guys. I think that we
should listen to Marlow.

964
01:15:07,056 --> 01:15:08,626
This is crazy.

965
01:15:09,961 --> 01:15:10,962
Hey.

966
01:15:10,987 --> 01:15:14,301
Your job is finding lost men, right?

967
01:15:18,054 --> 01:15:19,055
Okay, sir.

968
01:15:19,280 --> 01:15:21,432
But if we reach that position,
and he is not there...

969
01:15:21,457 --> 01:15:22,538
We don't send out a search party.

970
01:15:22,714 --> 01:15:24,628
We're back here by nightfall, understood?

971
01:15:24,842 --> 01:15:26,878
In 24 hours, we got to be
on the other side of this island.

972
01:15:27,088 --> 01:15:29,500
Roger that. Hear you loud and clear.

973
01:15:29,793 --> 01:15:32,698
Alright. You heard the man.
Moving out in 10.

974
01:15:32,913 --> 01:15:34,304
This is a good group of boys.

975
01:15:34,689 --> 01:15:36,509
We are all gonna die together out here.

976
01:15:36,784 --> 01:15:39,693
Good group of boys to die with.
I'll tell you that much.

977
01:15:40,834 --> 01:15:42,036
You should not have come here.

978
01:15:42,860 --> 01:15:44,921
when do you get to tell me
this is a bad idea?

979
01:15:45,563 --> 01:15:46,980
This is a bad idea.

980
01:16:22,989 --> 01:16:24,163
Yeah, you smell that?

981
01:16:24,782 --> 01:16:26,028
It's death.

982
01:16:29,410 --> 01:16:31,066
What the hell is this place?

983
01:16:31,382 --> 01:16:33,667
This is what left of Kong's parents.

984
01:16:33,914 --> 01:16:37,117
I have taken enough photos of mass graves,
to recognize one

985
01:16:37,619 --> 01:16:39,892
The crash site is just only
on other side of this valley

986
01:16:39,917 --> 01:16:42,380
We'll cross through and
make it to the highest point west.

987
01:16:42,924 --> 01:16:44,008
Uh oh.

988
01:16:44,910 --> 01:16:47,002
This place is a real no no, sir.

989
01:16:47,027 --> 01:16:48,707
We need to be going to the
north side right now.

990
01:16:48,732 --> 01:16:50,995
And you're welcome to do that, my man.

991
01:16:51,493 --> 01:16:52,493
By your self.

992
01:16:53,419 --> 01:16:56,359
I'm not leaving Jack out there.
Now, Who's with me?

993
01:16:57,984 --> 01:16:58,712
We can make it.

994
01:16:58,737 --> 01:17:00,209
You mightly right we can make it.

995
01:17:00,697 --> 01:17:03,227
Now stay sharp keep an eye out.

996
01:17:07,145 --> 01:17:09,349
I've only got here 28 years.
What do I know?

997
01:17:42,287 --> 01:17:43,186
Cole...

998
01:17:43,262 --> 01:17:45,370
Won't got time for that man.
Put the cigarette out.

999
01:17:58,703 --> 01:18:00,366
Watch those fumes!

1000
01:18:01,659 --> 01:18:02,829
Idiots.

1001
01:18:06,311 --> 01:18:08,084
Let's go. We gotta move!

1002
01:18:17,035 --> 01:18:18,036
Run!

1003
01:18:22,168 --> 01:18:23,169
In Here!

1004
01:18:28,539 --> 01:18:29,575
Quiet.

1005
01:18:50,517 --> 01:18:52,699
I told them to stand by
this was a no no.

1006
01:18:58,146 --> 01:18:59,160
Dammit.

1007
01:19:29,038 --> 01:19:30,039
Alright let's move.

1008
01:19:30,612 --> 01:19:31,758
** on me.

1009
01:19:33,719 --> 01:19:35,518
Alright, hurry up.

1010
01:19:36,583 --> 01:19:38,929
Somebody cover the civilians, quick
Let's Move!

1011
01:19:52,759 --> 01:19:53,760
Oh shit.

1012
01:19:56,562 --> 01:19:57,563
Randa!

1013
01:20:06,831 --> 01:20:07,833
Set up the 50!

1014
01:20:49,411 --> 01:20:52,167
For Meadow. **

1015
01:21:20,011 --> 01:21:22,052
Bring the torch! Do your thing!

1016
01:21:46,477 --> 01:21:47,722
Slivko!

1017
01:21:47,851 --> 01:21:48,673
Gas!

1018
01:21:48,802 --> 01:21:50,398
TOXIC GAS

1019
01:22:08,807 --> 01:22:10,590
Marlow!
The sword!

1020
01:22:36,217 --> 01:22:37,248
Slivko, Hang on!

1021
01:22:45,102 --> 01:22:46,194
This thing is moving!

1022
01:23:17,641 --> 01:23:18,807
Now look, Colonel.

1023
01:23:19,654 --> 01:23:21,576
You may out rank me...

1024
01:23:21,921 --> 01:23:24,423
but I've been here a hell a lot longer.

1025
01:23:24,581 --> 01:23:25,916
And I'm telling you...

1026
01:23:26,218 --> 01:23:29,477
that thing there just shredded us
was only the first of them

1027
01:23:29,664 --> 01:23:31,133
Now we are on their turf...

1028
01:23:31,342 --> 01:23:34,238
... And we need to turn back!
Turn sweet.

1029
01:23:34,327 --> 01:23:36,243
Not as long as Chapman still out there.

1030
01:23:36,268 --> 01:23:37,932
I'm Sorry, Colonel Packard.

1031
01:23:39,272 --> 01:23:40,805
Chapman is dead.

1032
01:23:46,902 --> 01:23:48,054
Nothing changes then!

1033
01:23:48,079 --> 01:23:50,316
We're still going to that crash site.

1034
01:23:50,550 --> 01:23:52,227
What's that in the crash site
that you want so badly?

1035
01:23:52,417 --> 01:23:53,418
Weapons!

1036
01:23:53,453 --> 01:23:55,011
Enough to kill it.

1037
01:23:55,036 --> 01:23:56,236
Kong didn't kill Chapman.

1038
01:23:56,261 --> 01:23:58,134
But It did kill these men!

1039
01:23:58,833 --> 01:24:00,756
My men!

1040
01:24:00,818 --> 01:24:02,059
You can't kill Kong, Colonel.

1041
01:24:02,448 --> 01:24:03,815
Kong is God on this island.

1042
01:24:04,090 --> 01:24:06,516
It is the only thing
keeping that lizard things underground.

1043
01:24:06,573 --> 01:24:08,627
He's right, Colonel. We can't kill Kong.

1044
01:24:08,816 --> 01:24:10,172
And that other creature?

1045
01:24:10,431 --> 01:24:12,748
That's the threat.
And there are more of them down here.

1046
01:24:12,998 --> 01:24:15,233
If you take away
that species' natural competition

1047
01:24:15,443 --> 01:24:16,685
they will proliferate out of control.

1048
01:24:16,802 --> 01:24:18,037
Then we will end them too!

1049
01:24:18,456 --> 01:24:20,428
After we bring this thing down.

1050
01:24:20,453 --> 01:24:21,707
I can not let you do that.

1051
01:24:21,777 --> 01:24:23,007
Wait! Hold your fire.

1052
01:24:26,649 --> 01:24:29,122
This is one war, we're not gonna lose.

1053
01:24:29,342 --> 01:24:30,343
It's nuts!

1054
01:24:30,368 --> 01:24:32,277
You hear me? This is nuts!

1055
01:24:32,302 --> 01:24:34,346
Please! You need to listen to him!

1056
01:24:34,371 --> 01:24:35,798
We are not at war, Colonel.
You are making a mistake.

1057
01:24:35,823 --> 01:24:37,385
Your lies got my men killed!

1058
01:24:37,542 --> 01:24:40,212
- And you're gonna get us all killed.
- It's not our fight.

1059
01:24:40,869 --> 01:24:42,616
Whose side are you on, Captain?

1060
01:24:42,644 --> 01:24:44,189
Okay, Colonel.

1061
01:24:45,126 --> 01:24:47,753
You will find your Sea Stallion
3 click off that ridge

1062
01:24:48,316 --> 01:24:51,025
Now, I'm gonna take these civillians
back to the boat.

1063
01:24:51,339 --> 01:24:52,716
And we wait for you there.

1064
01:24:53,248 --> 01:24:54,330
Alright?

1065
01:25:09,395 --> 01:25:10,396
Saddle up!

1066
01:25:11,290 --> 01:25:12,708
Let's go kill this thing!

1067
01:25:18,078 --> 01:25:19,180
Steve...

1068
01:25:19,402 --> 01:25:21,724
You running with the big dogs or
stayin' on the boat?

1069
01:25:23,008 --> 01:25:24,369
I don't wanna be on that porch.

1070
01:25:24,697 --> 01:25:25,877
Marlow, You okay?

1071
01:25:27,118 --> 01:25:28,619
We need to stop him.

1072
01:25:28,644 --> 01:25:31,817
You want to talk off him about it agian?
He seemed really good for it first time.

1073
01:25:32,158 --> 01:25:33,384
He is losing his grip.

1074
01:25:35,314 --> 01:25:36,522
Follow me...

1075
01:25:37,225 --> 01:25:38,836
We'll get off this rock alive.

1076
01:25:43,860 --> 01:25:44,861
Dear Billy...

1077
01:25:46,230 --> 01:25:48,503
I'm trying to get home with you and Mom.

1078
01:25:49,736 --> 01:25:51,204
Be strong.

1079
01:25:52,490 --> 01:25:53,856
I love you.

1080
01:26:00,897 --> 01:26:03,119
Make sure those get back to his family.

1081
01:26:04,436 --> 01:26:05,594
Dear Billy...

1082
01:26:08,270 --> 01:26:10,689
Your dad was one of the best to ever do it.

1083
01:26:18,382 --> 01:26:19,748
There is a water close by.

1084
01:26:20,324 --> 01:26:22,629
Are you lost? Which way?

1085
01:26:23,457 --> 01:26:24,557
Hang on.

1086
01:26:37,909 --> 01:26:38,939
Wait here.

1087
01:26:40,048 --> 01:26:42,078
Gonna get to high ground to find the river.

1088
01:26:43,960 --> 01:26:46,000
Hey! I'm coming too.

1089
01:26:47,162 --> 01:26:48,382
I'll be right here.

1090
01:26:51,501 --> 01:26:53,055
Keep your eyes open.

1091
01:26:54,063 --> 01:26:55,304
Up in the trees, too.

1092
01:26:56,190 --> 01:26:57,191
Why?

1093
01:26:57,516 --> 01:26:58,517
Ants.

1094
01:26:59,564 --> 01:27:00,607
Big ones.

1095
01:27:01,678 --> 01:27:02,679
There's one.

1096
01:27:04,326 --> 01:27:06,416
It sounds like a bird,
but it's a fucking ant.

1097
01:27:15,175 --> 01:27:18,294
Gather up everything you can,
including those seismic charges.

1098
01:27:19,195 --> 01:27:21,259
They got us attention the first one.

1099
01:27:35,579 --> 01:27:37,148
This is a bad idea.

1100
01:27:37,415 --> 01:27:38,603
Let's just get on with it

1101
01:27:39,413 --> 01:27:40,414
Mills, Cole...

1102
01:27:40,469 --> 01:27:41,556
Prep this ordnance.

1103
01:27:42,471 --> 01:27:45,487
Make him a special gift out of that Naplam.

1104
01:28:15,940 --> 01:28:18,159
The boat must be around that bend.

1105
01:30:10,816 --> 01:30:13,098
We have to go,
Now.

1106
01:30:44,425 --> 01:30:45,671
Don't shoot!

1107
01:30:48,111 --> 01:30:49,683
Conrad, which way are we going?

1108
01:30:49,708 --> 01:30:52,996
You said you need to get back to the boat.
It's that way.

1109
01:30:53,032 --> 01:30:54,423
Wait for us till dawn.

1110
01:30:54,856 --> 01:30:56,327
If we're not back by then...

1111
01:30:57,106 --> 01:30:58,132
Just go.

1112
01:30:59,570 --> 01:31:01,066
Where are you two going?

1113
01:31:02,962 --> 01:31:04,427
We gotta save Kong.

1114
01:31:05,846 --> 01:31:07,503
Not without me, pal.

1115
01:32:47,743 --> 01:32:48,744
Oh God.

1116
01:33:13,159 --> 01:33:14,160
Men!

1117
01:33:14,414 --> 01:33:15,891
Place the chargers.

1118
01:33:16,991 --> 01:33:18,702
It's time to show Kong...

1119
01:33:18,727 --> 01:33:22,127
... That man is king!

1120
01:33:22,790 --> 01:33:23,791
On one.

1121
01:33:24,253 --> 01:33:25,254
On Two.

1122
01:33:25,883 --> 01:33:26,884
On three.

1123
01:33:29,498 --> 01:33:30,499
Packard!

1124
01:33:36,626 --> 01:33:37,675
Don't do it.

1125
01:33:42,121 --> 01:33:44,534
Asked you fellas nice the first time.

1126
01:33:44,839 --> 01:33:46,161
We don't want to fight here, Packard.

1127
01:33:46,361 --> 01:33:48,334
This thing brought us down!
He killed my men!

1128
01:33:48,608 --> 01:33:50,428
Kong was just defending his territory.

1129
01:33:50,465 --> 01:33:52,062
We are soldiers!

1130
01:33:52,668 --> 01:33:53,829
We do the dirty work!

1131
01:33:53,854 --> 01:33:56,817
So our families and our countrymen
don't have to be afraid!

1132
01:33:56,962 --> 01:34:00,372
They should not even know that
a thing like this exists!

1133
01:34:00,706 --> 01:34:02,132
You've lost your mind.

1134
01:34:04,834 --> 01:34:06,643
Put that detonator down.

1135
01:34:20,346 --> 01:34:21,347
Stop!

1136
01:34:25,299 --> 01:34:27,367
The world is bigger than this.

1137
01:34:28,139 --> 01:34:29,519
Bitch, please!

1138
01:34:29,627 --> 01:34:32,117
Slivko, get her out of there!

1139
01:34:34,371 --> 01:34:37,107
You know it's the wrong thing to do, son.

1140
01:34:54,045 --> 01:34:55,046
Put it down, sir.

1141
01:34:55,598 --> 01:34:56,849
Packard!

1142
01:35:10,675 --> 01:35:11,676
Come on.

1143
01:35:12,606 --> 01:35:13,607
It's over.

1144
01:35:29,649 --> 01:35:30,730
That's the big one.

1145
01:35:31,166 --> 01:35:32,167
Fall back.

1146
01:35:35,777 --> 01:35:36,778
Go!

1147
01:35:46,966 --> 01:35:48,017
Colonel.

1148
01:35:49,338 --> 01:35:50,339
Sir!

1149
01:36:11,687 --> 01:36:13,999
Die you motherfucker...

1150
01:36:30,574 --> 01:36:32,624
- Kong.
- Kong's down. Let's go!

1151
01:36:38,247 --> 01:36:39,689
They told us to leave at dawn

1152
01:36:39,714 --> 01:36:41,113
- I know.
- It's dawn.

1153
01:36:41,138 --> 01:36:41,979
I know!

1154
01:36:42,004 --> 01:36:43,013
So what are we going to do?

1155
01:36:57,007 --> 01:36:58,370
This is the edge of the island.

1156
01:36:59,275 --> 01:37:02,413
Weaver, get up on those
rocks and fire a flare.

1157
01:37:02,738 --> 01:37:04,385
Well, then like, Brooks will see it.

1158
01:37:07,559 --> 01:37:08,900
I will buy you time.

1159
01:37:11,036 --> 01:37:12,211
This way.

1160
01:37:26,799 --> 01:37:29,150
Come on.
Every second counts.

1161
01:37:36,709 --> 01:37:37,710
Cole!

1162
01:37:37,939 --> 01:37:39,508
Come on, man, we gotta fall back.

1163
01:37:40,531 --> 01:37:41,736
Go live your life.

1164
01:37:42,074 --> 01:37:43,356
Get out of here.

1165
01:37:46,206 --> 01:37:47,207
- Cole, no!
- Cole!

1166
01:37:47,361 --> 01:37:48,378
- Cole, no!

1167
01:37:48,404 --> 01:37:51,084
- Cole!
- Cole!

1168
01:37:51,566 --> 01:37:53,441
No, don't!

1169
01:37:54,066 --> 01:37:55,993
Cole!

1170
01:37:56,320 --> 01:37:57,321
Cole!

1171
01:38:03,578 --> 01:38:06,631
Come on. Come on.
You son of a bitch.

1172
01:38:32,573 --> 01:38:33,960
Come on! Run!

1173
01:40:21,543 --> 01:40:22,977
Come on!
Run!

1174
01:40:25,804 --> 01:40:27,261
Come on! Hurry!

1175
01:40:34,480 --> 01:40:35,481
Come on!

1176
01:40:42,544 --> 01:40:43,546
Marlow, will you help me?

1177
01:41:35,150 --> 01:41:36,765
- Clear!
- Okay!

1178
01:41:39,284 --> 01:41:40,533
Come on, you bastard!

1179
01:42:31,858 --> 01:42:32,859
Weaver!

1180
01:44:21,984 --> 01:44:23,053
Weaver?

1181
01:44:23,078 --> 01:44:24,714
hey, hey hey!

1182
01:44:28,684 --> 01:44:29,711
You're okay?

1183
01:45:21,004 --> 01:45:22,781
So what do you think fellas?

1184
01:45:23,052 --> 01:45:24,602
This way to Key West?

1185
01:45:25,983 --> 01:45:27,359
I think it is, brother.

1186
01:45:28,985 --> 01:45:30,244
This place will change.

1187
01:45:31,470 --> 01:45:32,933
Word will get out.

1188
01:45:33,619 --> 01:45:34,621
It always does.

1189
01:45:35,500 --> 01:45:37,409
No, it's not coming from us.

1190
01:45:42,362 --> 01:45:45,997
We will meet again.

1191
01:45:47,201 --> 01:45:49,325
Don't know where.

1192
01:45:49,425 --> 01:45:52,313
Don't know when.

1193
01:45:52,573 --> 01:45:55,880
But I know we'll meet again.

1194
01:48:27,807 --> 01:48:29,289
<i>If you want to see a cub go crazy...</i>

1195
01:48:29,539 --> 01:48:32,182
<i>see what happens if this
guy gets paid well.</i>

1196
01:48:33,343 --> 01:48:35,145
<i>High ball, great hit.</i>

1197
01:48:38,974 --> 01:48:43,042
<i>An the impossible dream
just became possible!</i>
